LINK: https://leetcode.com/problems/duplicate-emails/description/?envType=problem-list-v2&envId=v9r4nua2
TYPE: Easy

==> My approach:
import pandas as pd

def duplicate_emails(person: pd.DataFrame) -> pd.DataFrame:
    # Count person by email
    person_count = person.groupby('email').size().reset_index(name='count')

    # Filter duplicate emails
    duplicate = person_count[person_count['count'] > 1][['email']]

    return duplicate
